<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>How does mail get to individual employees?</h3>
<h3></h3>
<ol>
<li>BYU - Idaho receives mail that has 83460 for the zip code</li>
<li>University mail is sorted by a 4 digit mail stop number assigned to each department</li>
<li>Mail Services delivers mail to department secretaries</li>
<li>Department secretaries distribute your mail to your box</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What is the 4-digit mail stop for your department?</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>For the list of assigned mail stops by department, <a href="x51337.xml">click here.</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What address should you use?</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>When you have something shipped to BYU&ndash;Idaho, it is important that your address shows information that will help us to expedite your mail to you. Some couriers need a physical address, such as Fedex or UPS. When we receive your mail your 4-digit mail stop helps us sort and deliver your mail to the correct place. It will be important for you to use the following example when ordering online, subscribing to magazines, or verbally giving your information over the phone.<a href="x51357.xml"> For example click here</a></p>
